The article highlights the establishment of the Continental Army in 1775 and its role in fighting for American independence. It recognizes the United States Army for its contributions to national security and the American way of life over the past 245 years. The article also commemorates the 75th anniversary of the conclusion of World War II and the Army's crucial role in the Allied Forces' victory. It pays tribute to the soldiers who sacrificed their lives to defend freedom. The article acknowledges the Army's efforts in responding to the coronavirus pandemic, including the creation of alternate care facilities, deployment of healthcare professionals, and research for countermeasures. Finally, it celebrates the bravery and sacrifice of all soldiers, past and present, and wishes the United States Army a happy 245th birthday.